## Requirements

Building the API client library requires:
1. Java 1.7+
2. Maven/Gradle/SBT

## Installation

To install the API client library to your local Maven repository, simply execute:

```shell
mvn clean install
```

To deploy it to a remote Maven repository instead, configure the settings of the repository and execute:

```shell
mvn clean deploy
```

Refer to the [OSSRH Guide](http://central.sonatype.org/pages/ossrh-guide.html) for more information.

### Maven users

Add this dependency to your project's POM:

```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.openapitools</groupId>
    <artifactId>openapi-client</artifactId>
    <version>0.1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
    <scope>compile</scope>
</dependency>
```

### Gradle users

Add this dependency to your project's build file:

```groovy
compile "org.openapitools:openapi-client:0.1.0-SNAPSHOT"
```

### SBT users

```scala
libraryDependencies += "org.openapitools" % "openapi-client" % "0.1.0-SNAPSHOT"
```

*Zones* | **setRecordsOfRrset** | **POST** /zones/${idOrNamePathParam}/rrsets/${rrNamePathParam}/${rrTypePathParam}/actions/set_records | Set Records of an RRSet
*Zones* | **updateRecordsOfRrset** | **POST** /zones/${idOrNamePathParam}/rrsets/${rrNamePathParam}/${rrTypePathParam}/actions/update_records | Update Records of an RRSet
